    "content": "IF the user requests a refund to a payment method other than the original payment method THEN: - FIRST, inspect the order's payment_history (via get_order_details) to determine the original payment method before attempting any refund/return tool call. - IF the original payment method for the order is a gift card THEN do not perform the refund to an alternate non-gift-card method and inform the user of the policy that refunds to gift-card-paid orders must go back to the original gift card (or another existing gift card); offer to proceed with refund to the original/another gift card and do not call the action tool with a non-gift payment_method_id. - OTHERWISE (original payment method is a credit/debit card or other non-gift method) it is permissible to process the refund or exchange settlement to an alternate card/payment method at the user's request; include the requested payment_method_id when invoking the action tool.",
    "rationale": "Trajectories showed a failed tool call when attempting to refund to a non-original method; proactively checking order payment history avoids errors and ensures policy (gift-card refunds) is enforced before invoking return/refund tools.",
