    "section": "action_execution",
    "target_id": null,
    "content": "IF the user requests an exchange/modify AND the user has specified constraints for the replacement (e.g., same difficulty level, specific theme, exact color/size, or other attribute requirements) THEN: (1) call get_product_details(product_id) to inspect candidate replacement variants; (2) verify that the chosen replacement variant(s) exactly satisfy the user's stated constraints before passing new_item_ids to the exchange/modify tool; (3) IF no available variant fully meets the constraints, inform the user, present the closest available alternatives that do meet as many constraints as possible, and ask the user to confirm which alternative to use; (4) IF the user confirms a replacement that does NOT meet one or more previously stated constraints, explicitly restate the mismatched attributes and require an explicit confirmation to proceed.",
    "rationale": "Trajectory 1 executed an exchange for a jigsaw puzzle variant whose difficulty level did not match the user's explicit request to keep the same difficulty; the system must verify replacements satisfy user-specified constraints and prompt when they do not.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      "Conversation 1"
    ]
  },
  {
